      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DAWN RETREAT (5) produced a reasonable effort to finish 1.75 lengths away in fourth last start over 1205m at this track when he did his best work late. That followed a first-up win at this track. Has his share of talent. Hard to beat in this suitable race. DENVER AFFAIR (3) is putting together some solid results. Finished second at Port Hedland two starts back then got the job done by half a length as favourite last time out over 1103m at this track. Suitably placed so anticipating another big run. KIA ORA TATOU (4) was second up last start and went close, beaten a long neck into third at this track over 1205m. Should be nearing his peak at this stage of the campaign. HOPE TO ADMIRE (6) was responsible for a better run last start, beaten 3 lengths into fourth over 1400m at Port Hedland. Capable of featuring prominently. ADRETT (2) is racing well without winning and has to be included.",
